## Resumen

Backend Node.js con Fastify, validación Zod, ORM Drizzle. Arquitectura en capas estrictas. Type-safe end-to-end.

## Capas (direccionalidad estricta)

```
HTTP request
    ↓
routes/         (Fastify, validación request)
    ↓
services/       (lógica de negocio, puro TS)
    ↓
repositories/   (Drizzle queries)
    ↓
Postgres
```

Nunca hacia arriba. Service nunca toca `request/reply`. Repository nunca conoce service.

## Patrón de route

```typescript
// routes/budgets.routes.ts
import { FastifyPluginAsync } from "fastify";
import { CreateBudgetSchema, BudgetSchema } from "@/schemas/budgets.schema";
import { budgetsService } from "@/services/budgets.service";

export const budgetsRoutes: FastifyPluginAsync = async (app) => {
    app.post("/budgets", {
        schema: { body: CreateBudgetSchema, response: { 201: BudgetSchema } },
    }, async (req, reply) => {
        const userId = req.user.id;  // de @fastify/jwt
        const budget = await budgetsService.create(userId, req.body);
        reply.code(201).send(budget);
    });
};
```

## Service pattern

```typescript
// services/budgets.service.ts
import { budgetsRepository } from "@/repositories/budgets.repository";
import { CreateBudget } from "@/schemas/budgets.schema";
import { AppError } from "@/lib/errors";

export const budgetsService = {
    async create(userId: string, input: CreateBudget) {
        if (input.amount <= 0) throw new AppError("Amount must be positive", 400);
        return budgetsRepository.insert({ ...input, userId });
    },
};
```

## Auth (JWT)

```typescript
// server.ts
app.register(jwt, { secret: process.env.JWT_SECRET });
app.addHook("onRequest", async (req) => {
    if (req.url.startsWith("/auth/")) return;
    await req.jwtVerify();
});
```

## Error handling

Handler global mapea `AppError` → HTTP status. Pino loggea con `req.id`.

